sentences: Blanche Ray Alden (July 5, 1870 – 1934) was an American pianist and composer, who published under the pseudonym Theodora Dutton.
Her short piano piece, Christmas Day Secrets, is the only work in the Suzuki Piano Repertoire attributed to a female composer.
